The Speaker of Osun State House of Assembly, Hon Timothy Owoeye, on Monday said the bill on Amotekun security outfit would be given speedy hearing and passage by the state legislature. He said the legislature was still awaiting the bill from the executive after its recent harmonisation by the Commissioners for Justice in the southwest states. ALSO READ: Equatorial Guinea leader’s son fined 30m euros, suspended jail confirmed Osun Assembly screens Egbemode, Omowaye, seven other… Speaking through his Chief Press Secretary (CPS), Mr. Kunle Alabi, Owoeye maintained that “we are yet to receive the bill from the executive. But, I can assure you that as soon as we receive the bill, it will be given expeditious hearing and passage.” According to him, “presently, the House is on recess. However, we are ready to cut short our recess and do the needful the moment we get hold of the bill. Owoeye further added that anything that has to do with the security of the citizenry must be given topmost priority by the government, stressing that Amotekun Bill should be given necessary legislative support and backing. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE TO GET IT!!! STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. CLICK HERE NOW TO WORK FROM HOME ENTIRELY AT YOUR OWN CONVINIENCE AND GET PAID WEEKLY, DIRECTLY INTO YOUR SPECIFIED BANK ACCOUNT.REGISTRATION IS ABSOLUTELY FREE.